column51: company_description
KACE Networks, Inc. operates as a systems management appliance company.
Thwapr provides a machine-to-machine (M2M) service that allows users to share videos and photos with friends.
Zinch is a website connecting colleges and students by allowing students to create their profiles that can be browsed by colleges.
Cloud.com develops an open source cloud orchestration software product for the implementation of cloud computing environments.
Wildfire is a provider of enterprise social media marketing software.
Authenticlick is a web analytics company providing web traffic quality intelligence solutions for online advertising optimization.
Idooble.com was a social commerce platform that enabled interactive shopping.
BioSeek provides cell-based human disease models for drug discovery and development.
Xkoto is a technology platform that enables its users to replicate and visualize their data.
Coradiant provides network and website monitoring equipment to manage, optimize and troubleshoot web applications.
QuantaLife is a biotechnology company that manufactures and markets products based on their proprietary nucleic acid testing method.
BroadLight is a supplier of communication semiconductors and optical transceivers for cost-effective FTTP (Fiber-to-the-Premises).
BBE, a producer and distributor of original, web-based programming solutions, offers a platform for serving, tracking and managing ads.
TelASIC Communications develops remote radio head products for WCDMA/HSDPA and WiMAX/LTE infrastructure applications.
LegiTime Technologies provides LegiText, a subscription-based SMS solution with message authentication, and archiving facilities.
Mobius Microsystems offers CMOS Harmonic Oscillator, a technology enabling system designers to create minute and mechanical robust products.
Boonty is a developer of online casual games that focus on enhancing social interactions.
B-Side Entertainment operates as a distributor of independent films in the United States.
Taggstr provided students with a mobile application to find information on the best deals around their university through tagging.
Fashism, an online platform, enables its fashion enthusiasts to share styles and get their images rated.
Goodmail Systems provides an email service for consumers to identify authentic messages from legitimate commercial and non-profit senders.
Nirvanix offers cloud storage solutions to avoid downtime losses for customers expecting security reliability and redundancy levels.
Founder & CEO of LookStat. We help photographers and agencies make more money.
Sweepery offers a platform that enables users to integrate, serve, and optimize websites and conversion rates.
Luminary Micro designs, markets and sells ARM Cortex-M3-based microcontrollers for energy, security, and connectivity markets.
ZettaCore, pioneering the field of molecular electronics, is focused on developing molecular materials for the electronics industry.
Clicker is an online platform for viewing TV shows, reading episode reviews, keeping up with breaking news, and joining fan communities.
Ikoa provided low-power, high-performance semiconductor products for consumer mobile devices.
SocialShield offers tools that give parents a 360° view of their kids social networking activities.
LeisureLogix offers RoadTrip Wizard, an application built on technology that marries trip booking, location-based content and navigation.
Storwize is a provider of real-time data compression solutions that boost storage space on network storage environments.
AutoVirt develops a software solution to assess, migrate and manage unstructured data stored on NAS devices and Windows file servers.
Loopt is a mobile application and website that connects people to their community.
Blue Lane Technologies provides vulnerability shields for physical and virtual server infrastructure.
Socialcast is an enterprise collaboration web app that allows users to track and integrate company data, users and apps in real-time.
Collective Intellect is a digital communications analytics platform addressing the needs of marketers and researchers.
Wavii provides an iPhone app enabling users to follow and receive updates on topics such as celebrities, companies, and politicians.
Seesmic provides social media management and collaboration tools that enable businesses to build and manage their brands online.
Apnex Medical manufactures and markets active implantable medical devices for the treatment of obstructive sleep apnea.
OneTwoSee also known as MobileReactor,  is a Philadelphia-based company that sits at the intersection of digital media, sports and technology.
Echopass is an app service provider offering web-based telephone and Internet customer support services, including email and web call-backs.
ID Analytics is a company providing credit and identity risk management solutions for real-time information services.
Vela Systems offers software that automates the execution and oversight of field activities on construction and capital projects.
FlowCardia designs and develops catheter-based technologies for the treatment of totally occluded coronary and peripheral arteries.
Bizanga is a provider of email and message management platforms.
Transpond enables brands to create, publish, manage and track engagement with their content across social and mobile platforms.
Caterva, a development stage company, intends to develop a real-time social marketing platform.
Innovative Silicon develops and commercializes Floating Body effect memory for SoC/MPU products used in diverse applications.
Kardia Health Systems is a healthcare information technology firm offering the delivery of specialty medicine for cardiology.
Biolex Therapeutics developed therapeutic proteins and monoclonal antibodies that had been optimized to enhance their efficacy and potency.
FoldRx Pharmaceuticals is focused on discovering and developing disease-modifying drug therapies for protein misfolding diseases.
Klir Technologies provides information technology management solutions through a software-as-a-service business model.
MetaCarta provides technology to identify geographic references in content enabling monetization, localization, and finding information.
Viridity Software is an energy management company enabling businesses to map datacenter infrastructure while optimizing power consumption.
Devtap is focused on developing a semantic search engine.
Bebo is a social networking platform. The company enables members to connect friends, as well as share photos and discover new interests.
SideTour provides a community marketplace enabling users to find and host activities such as tours, dine- outs and rides with other users.
SARcode Bioscience develops an antigen for the treatment of unmet medical needs in ophthalmology, dermatology and inflammatory diseases.
Lore is an online learning platform where learners and instructors can share educational content in a simple and social online environment.
Pelago offers Whrrl v2.0, an app that enables people to capture and share moments, as they happen, in story form.
Desk.com is the all-in-one customer support app for fast-growing companies
Trinity Biosystems develops oral therapeutic proteins and vaccines for respiratory, digestive and sexually transmitted diseases.
Virtual Computer provides intelligent desktop virtualization solutions.
Oasys Mobile develops, publishes, and aggregates mobile phone games, touch and mobile media applications, and related services.
Gamook is a platform enabling people to play and share online casual games.
Quattro Wireless, a global mobile advertising company, enables advertisers and publishers to reach and engage their target audiences.
ShopWell is a personalized nutrition app that recommends food based on a user's dietary needs and helps them build healthy grocery lists.
Newsbasis is a communications platform for journalists to connect with companies they write about.
NEXX Systems provides processing systems and technologies for wafer-level packaging applications.
5min Media is a syndication platform for lifestyle, knowledge and instructional videos.
MyCabbage is an online and mobile platform for storing, tracking, sharing, and selling deals among friends.
Gotuit is a provider of metadata technology that optimizes the value of stored video libraries for professional content publishers.
TeleCIS Wireless develops wireless system-on-a-chip solutions for the fixed, portable and mobile broadband wireless communications markets.
Snapette is a mobile shopping application for finding and sharing fashion products available in neighborhood stores.
EmSense provides scalable physiological and brainwave measurement technology.
MakerBot Industries creates open source 3D printers.
Image Space Media offers in-image advertising, an ad solution pairing brand messages with contextually relevant images to reach audiences.
Wanderfly is a web platform for discovering and sharing personalized travel recommendations.
Walkby is an online network of retailers that enables customers to search for products and have them delivered.
FameCast is an interactive, branded entertainment platform focusing on contest-centered marketing campaigns.
Cassat provides software solutions and technologies for operating green data centers.
VirtuOz, a digital customer relationships platform, provides intelligent virtual agents for enterprises to ensure quality user experience.
SolFocus is a manufacturer of solar energy systems based on concentrator photovoltaic (CPV) technology.
Nimbula delivers cloud infrastructure software enabling enterprises and service providers to build private, public or hybrid clouds.
Giftiki is a social commerce platform and a collaborative gifting engine that enables users to contribute toward a collective fund.
StorSpeed develops products to increase network storage performance.
ts products are cloud-based management systems for spas and salons.
Jajah is a VoIP provider enabling users to make international and long-distance calls at local rates.
Baxano develops minimally-invasive tools to restore spine function and preserve healthy tissues.
RipCode provided a dual application infrastructure solution for delivering video on-demand and real-time video streaming.
VeteranCentral, an online community, delivered applications and information to support veterans of various fields in resolving issues.
RippleFunction enabled conference and event organisers to sell tickets through Twitter and Facebook promotions.
CV Ingenuity was a medical device company that developed drug-coated balloon platforms for the touch-and-go treatment of vascular diseases.
AdexLink is a mobile marketing platform for ads mediation and app cross-promotion.
Certeon provided appliance software solutions that eliminated traditional network constraints and accelerated application performance.
Applied Identity develops identity-aware network security solutions.
Prenova provides energy management solutions helping companies to control their energy spend.
WooMe is an online dating app that connects people who have common ground.
Help Me Rent is a social community and interactive publication where people can post, search, and book rental appointments.
Mail.com, a web portal and web-based email service, offers news articles and videos and a free webmail application with unlimited storage.
DubMeNow is a mobile software solution used to exchange business cards and instantaneously manage contact information.
Calxeda (previously known as Smooth-Stone)was a company that aimed to provide computers based on the ARM architecture for server computers.
